# Creevo Landing Page - Project Structure

## Architecture Overview
This is a React + TypeScript + Vite landing page application that:
- Uses Vite for development and building
- Serves static files via Express on port 8010
- Is deployed to GCP VM using PM2 process management
- Uses Nginx reverse proxy for domain routing (creevo.app)

## Key Files and Directories
- **Entry Point**: [src/main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx) - React app entry
- **Main Component**: [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Root component
- **Landing Page**: [src/pages/landing/index.tsx](mdc:src/pages/landing/index.tsx) - Main landing page component
- **Landing Styles**: [src/pages/landing/LandingPage.css](mdc:src/pages/landing/LandingPage.css) - Landing page styles
- **Theme System**: [src/theme/theme.ts](mdc:src/theme/theme.ts) - Color palette and theme tokens
- **Server**: [server.js](mdc:server.js) - Express server for production
- **PM2 Config**: [ecosystem.config.cjs](mdc:ecosystem.config.cjs) - PM2 process configuration
- **Assets**: [public/assets/](mdc:public/assets/) - Static assets (logo.png, main_page.png)

## Important Notes
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) has `"type": "module"` - all JS files use ES modules
- PM2 config file MUST be `.cjs` extension (not `.js`) due to ES module setup
- Build output goes to `dist/` directory (gitignored)
- Server serves static files from `dist/` directory
